@{PARD}
@{B}MONSTERNAME Habitat/Society:@{UB}@{PAR}

Rapiertails prefer more temperate climates and are more likely to be found in
warmer regions. Rapiertails are excellent warriors and they know it. They love
killing for any reason and have learned to appreciate treasure. Not so much as a
means of worth but a way of showing of power. They make their homes almost
anywhere, sides of cliffs, in caves, on islands, and in large trees. They lair
the area with the treasures they have collected and build nest. They do not
appricate anything find their nest and kill all that enter it, including other
rapiertails.@{PAR}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Ecology" "MONSTERNAME Ecology"
@{CODE}	@{" Picture         " LINK "ImpPro:Data/ExtMonsterData/MONSTERNAME.iff/main"}@{" Stats           " LINK "Stats"}
	@{" Combat          " LINK "Combat"}@{" Habitat/Society " LINK "Habitat"}@{" Ecology         " LINK "Ecology"}

@{PARD}
@{B}MONSTERNAME Ecology:@{UB}@{PAR}

Rapiertails will be found together for a short time when mating. In this case
their will be two parents and one or two eggs or hatchlings. Hatchlings are born
with 2 tails (use a 1d3 to determine hit points) and do only half damage and can
only move half the normal speed. Depending on how old they are hatchlings
normally will not know how to fly (mainly because shortly after learning to fly
they leave to live on their own.) When mating the rapiertails will have a nest
built to have their young born in where their treasure will not be located. Just
because two rapiertails share a moment doesn't mean they are going to trust the
other.@{PAR}

@ENDNODE

